The paper discusses a method for summarizing data using itemsets, which is a common task in data mining and machine learning. The use of a probabilistic maximum entropy model and iterative updating procedure suggests a focus on machine learning and probabilistic modeling, which are common topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of itemsets and mining on-the-fly suggests a focus on data mining and databases, which are common topics in cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the use of summaries and information retrieval suggests a focus on information retrieval, which is a common topic in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
